parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the malfunction or non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: The SRS (Supplemental Restraint System) light remains illuminated
the airbag warning light is on
the airbag system is inoperative
the passenger side airbag may not deploy
the seat belts and airbags may malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can lead to delays in addressing safety issues, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Parts are not available for recall repairs
dealerships are unable to inspect or repair vehicles
owners are left without a solution for an extended period.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Poor service and repair practices can lead to further damage to the vehicle, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Dealerships ignore or fail to address recall safety issues
improper diagnosis or repair of issues
unnecessary repairs or replacement of parts
poor communication with customers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts off while driving
especially when decelerating or coming to a stop; the transmission slams or clunks into limp-home mode
resulting in little acceleration from a stop; the vehicle is unable to shift gears properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PCM can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off while driving
especially when accelerating from a stop; the vehicle is unable to start; the main fuel relay needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start; the ignition switch needs to be turned multiple times before the vehicle starts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS module can cause the ABS and VSA system warning lights to illuminate, potentially leading to a loss of braking ability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light and VSA system warning light are illuminated
the vehicle's brake system may malfunction
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to suddenly drop to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal suddenly drops to the floor
the vehicle is difficult to stop
the vehicle may lose control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear ABS wheel sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, potentially leading to a loss of braking ability and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The ABS warning light is illuminated
the vehicle's brake system may malfunction
and the brake pedal may feel soft or spongy.
